{"title": "Missing SSL certificate verification", "summary": "  Applications processing sensitive data should use valid SSL certificates. This rule checks if SSL verification is enabled. ", "description": "\n\nApplications processing sensitive data should use valid SSL certificates.\nThis rule checks if SSL verification is enabled.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Do not disable SSL certificate validation in your HTTP client\n\n\u2705 Ensure verification of both peers and hostnames is enabled in your HTTP client:\n\n```php\ncurl_setopt($curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER, true);\ncurl_setopt($curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST, true);\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-295"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_ssl_verification"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}